    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prayers intended to be chanted or sung, used in Christian worship; sources of the prayers are the Bible (other than Psalms) and other certain texts. Examples of these scriptural hymns are the Song of Moses from the Old Testament, the Benedictus from the New Testament, and the Lord's Prayer.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045248/Bowker, Oxford Dictionary of World Religions (1997)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046363/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (1994-2001)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Oraciones o canciones usadas en misas cristianas provenientes de la Biblia (u otros Salmos) y algunos otros textos. Ejemplos de estos himnos textuales escritos son el Cántico de Moisés del Antiguo Testamento, el Benedictus del Nuevo Testamento y Oraciones al Señor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gebeden of gezangen die bij de christelijke eredienst worden gebruikt en uit de Bijbel (niet de Psalmen) en andere teksten afkomstig zijn. Voorbeelden van dergelijke Bijbelse gezangen zijn het Lied van Mozes uit het Oude Testament, het Benedictus uit het Nieuwe Testament, en het Onze Vader.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000120595/Wikipedia (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Im christlichen Gottesdienst verwendetes Gebet oder Lied aus der Bibel (ausgenommen den Psalmen) und aus bestimmten anderen Texten. Beispiele solcher biblischen Liedtexte sind das Lied des Mose aus dem Alten Testament, das Benedictus aus dem Neuen Testament und das Vaterunser.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用於基督教禮拜儀式的祈禱文或歌曲，來自於聖經（詩篇除外）及其他特定文本。這些出自聖經讚美詩文本的例子有：舊約聖經的摩西之歌 (Song of Moses)、新約聖經的以色列頌(Benedictus)和天主經(Lord’s Prayer)。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Orações destinadas a serem cantadas ou  usadas na adoração cristã; as fontes das orações são a Bíblia (exceto Salmos) e outros certos textos. Exemplos desses hinos das escrituras são a Canção de Moisés do Velho Testamento, o Benedictus do Novo Testamento e a Oração do Senhor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
